<section aria-labelledby="problem-heading" class="px-4 py-24 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
    <h2 id="problem-heading" class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text sm:text-4xl">
      What is release assurance for an AI-built app?
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
      Release assurance is a review record that states which authorized checks ran, what they covered, the evidence behind each result, and what a retest established before a release ships.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
      That distinction matters when coding agents can change an application faster than a team can review it. A list of alerts still leaves the hardest questions unanswered: what was actually exercised, what is only suspected, whether the fix held, and what can be shown to a client or reviewer.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
